  <recitals>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>The Stockbridge-Munsee Community is a federally recognized Indian tribe with inherent sovereign powers and is governed by the Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Council pursuant to the 1937 Constitution, as amended;</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>The Stockbridge-Munsee Community has the authority under its Constitution and its inherent rights as a sovereign nation to adopt and amend	Ordinances;</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>Chapter 13, Truancy, establishes the Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Law on Truancy;</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>The Tribal Council wishes to ensure required attendance by school aged children; and</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>The Tribal Council also wishes to ensure that families of school aged children receive the support and encouragement they need to ensure the required attendance of the household's school aged children;</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>NOW THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED,</conjunction>
      <text>the Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Council hereby adopts the amendments to Chapter 13, which make the following changes:</text>
      <text>
        <ul proof="needed">
          <li>The following new sections were added:  <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.5" proof="needed">13.5</cite> was modified and renumbered as <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.5|(A)" proof="needed">13.5(A)</cite> with new subsections (1) and (2) added; <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.6|(N)" proof="needed">13.6 (N)</cite> and (O); and <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.13|(E)" proof="needed">13.13 (E)</cite>.</li>
          <li>The following sections were amended:  <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.1" proof="needed">13.1</cite>; <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.4" proof="needed">13.4</cite>; <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.6|(C)" proof="needed">13.6 (C)</cite>, (D), (E), (G), and (J); <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.8" proof="needed">13.8</cite>; <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.9|(B)" proof="needed">13.9(B)</cite>; <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.10|(C)" proof="needed">13.10 (C)</cite>; <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.11" proof="needed">13.11</cite>; and <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.13|(A-D)" proof="needed">13.13 (A-D)</cite>.</li>
          <li>The following materials were deleted:  <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.3" proof="needed">13.3</cite>; and <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.6|(M)" proof="needed">13.6 (M)</cite>.</li>
          <li>The following materials were renumbered or had numbering added: <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.6|(N)" proof="needed">13.6 (N)</cite> as (M); <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.10" proof="needed">13.10</cite>; <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.11" proof="needed">13.11</cite>; and <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.14" proof="needed">13.14</cite> was renumbered as <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.14|(A)" proof="needed">13.14 (A)</cite> and <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.15" proof="needed">13.15</cite> was renumbered to be <cite doc="Stockbridge-Munsee Tribal Code" path="13.14|(B)" proof="needed">13.14 (B)</cite>.</li>
        </ul>
      </text>
    </recital>
  </recitals>
